genresAdvancedInfo.name: sinhala edm
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Sinhala EDM is a subgenre of electronic dance music that originated in Sri Lanka. It combines traditional Sinhalese music with modern electronic beats and production techniques. The result is a high-energy, danceable sound that is popular in nightclubs and at festivals. Sinhala EDM often features vocals in the Sinhalese language and incorporates elements of traditional Sri Lankan instruments such as the rabana and thammattama.
